/bin/bash -lc "rg -n \"\\"'$'"\\"'$" content/papers/second.law.md' in /home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive succeeded in 51ms:
1:---
2:title: "The Second Law as Physical Fact and as Human Inference"
3:author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
4:year: 1990
5:abstract: >
6:  We try to correct some persistent misconceptions which are preventing
7:  progress in current research. These include failure to take note of
8:  highly cogent facts and theorems, semantic confusions over
9:  terminology, and clinging to folklore long after it is obsolete.
10:---
11:## Introduction {#introduction .unnumbered}
12:In spite of the spectacular advances in experimental techniques all
13:about us, we live in an age of inexplicable decadence where theory is
14:concerned. A wild variety of different views about entropy and
15:reversibility, their place in fundamental physics, and the role of
16:information for science in general, is being expressed. But important
17:facts that were well understood and clearly explained by Maxwell and
18:Gibbs over 100 years ago, and which played a crucial role in the work of
19:Planck and Einstein 80 years ago, have been lost and are no longer
20:comprehended at all by some who try to work in this area.
