codex
Edits applied to `content/papers/second.law.md` only.

Summary of changes:
- Improved markdown structure/readability with minimal paragraph separation fixes (added blank-line paragraph breaks where prose/list transitions were clearly intended).
- Added display-equation numbering markup (`\tag{...}`) so in-text equation references are discoverable, including tags for:
  - `(1)`, `(2)`, `(12)`, `(14)`, `(15)`, `(17)`, `(19)`, `(20)`, `(21)`, `(22)`, `(23)`, `(26)`
- Kept all mathematical expressions, symbols, operators, and equation content unchanged.
- Cleaned display-math block formatting so Hugo+KaTeX rendering is more reliable (equations on their own blocks with surrounding blank lines).
- No duplicate abstract text found in body, so none removed.
- No figure handling changes (ignored as requested).
- No citation-footnote double-patterns were present, so no citation normalization changes were required.

Self-check:
- Paragraph boundaries now use blank lines where intended.
- No unresolved in-text equation references among equation citations in this file (non-equation list numbering like reversible meanings `(1)/(2)/(3)` remains prose list numbering).
